    PG2000  MAIN MENU FUNCTIONS

    <FILE><Import Library>:
    Before you can use the function blocks and/or Inline functions of a library
    in your project, you must import the library into the appropriate project
    databank. To do this, use the function <File><Import Library>. After this
    function has been called, all *.SLB files (libraries) located under the path
    C:\PG2000\LIBRARY\ are displayed in a file selection box. After the desired
    library has been selected, it is imported into the current project data
    bank. The appropriate *.SLB file is put in the directory for standard
    libraries of the current project (<Project Name>.PGP\DBK\LIBFILES). The
    importation progress of indivdual objects, which the library contains, is
    displayed in the message line.

    The system library is already automatically imported into the databank
    when a project is created. This means that the functions of the system
    library are available immediately after the project has been created.




