.114
    PG2000  MAIN MENU FUNCTIONS

    <OBJECT><Parameters><Start (Irq/Exc) No.>:
    The start number determines in which order the tasks on the PCC are to be
    started (boot behavior of the PCC). This means that you can set the order
    of the tasks within a task class using the start number. The numerical value
    can be between 0 and 128, and is interpreted as follows:

    - Tasks with the lowest numbers are processed first.
    - Tasks with the same numbers are put in order in relation to the other
      tasks. However, the order of tasks with the same number is not fixed.
    - Tasks with number 0 are processed at some point within a cycle.

    Value 0 is entered by default.
    The appropriate exception number is entered for EXCEPTION TASKS
    (EXC object) here.
    The module number (address of the module which generates the interrupt) is
    entered for INTERRUPT TASKS (IRQ object).



