                        is automatically installed onto the PCC after every 
                        download or boot procedure. This means that the task is
                        started either automatically or manually (by the user)
                        depending on the entry in the <Start> box.
    Don't Install:      With this setting, the task is located on the PCC after
                        a download, but it is not executable.
                        This means that the task must be manually installed by
                        the user after each download or boot procedure, using
                        the <Install> function of the PCC monitor. Procedure:
                           1. Call the <Target><Monitor> function 
                           2. Select task class with the <ENTER> key
                           3. Select task and press the <SPACE> bar
                           4. call the <Install> function
                        Only then can the task be manually started using the
                        <Restart> function of the PCC monitor.


