    <OBJECT><Parameters><Configure><Module><Logbook entries>:
    All fatal errors which occur within an application (PCCSW error like
    cycle time violations, installation errors etc.), are reported by the
    operating system. This report is put in its own error logbook, and can
    be read using the <Target><Analysis> function.
    You can define the maximum number of error logbook entries in the entry
    field <Logbook entries>. This means that if you enter the value 20 in
    this box, the most recent 20 PCCSW errors in the error logbook will be
    reported. Older entries are overwritten. Only the values 16 to 500 are
    allowed for the number of error logbook entries!

    <OBJECT><Parameters><Configure><Module><Cyclic tasks>:
    You can set the maximum number of cyclic tasks (standard tasks, high-speed
    task classes, interrupt and exception tasks) which can be installed on the
    PCC in this entry field. If you try to install more cyclic tasks than are
    defined in this entry field, the installation process is interrupted by
    an error message.


    @148[ Module ]                          @052[ MM Object ]                     @001[ Overview ]
.150
    PG2000  MAIN MENU FUNCTIONS

    <OBJECT><Parameters><Configure><Module><Idle time tasks>:
    The maximum number of non-cyclic application tasks (also called idle time
    tasks) which can be installed on the PCC is set in this field.
    If you try to install more non-cyclic application tasks than are defined
    in this entry field, the installation process is interrupted by an error
    message. Idle time tasks use the system's so-called idle time. This means:
    idle time tasks are only carried out if neither the operating system nor
    the cyclic tasks need CPU time (system time).

    <OBJECT><Parameters><Configure><Module><System Tasks>:
    The maximum number of system tasks which can be installed on the PCC is set
    in this field. System tasks include spooler (for handling intelligent I/O
    processors), debugger and profiler runtime module. The operating system
    itself installs several system tasks by default. This means that if you
    install additional system tasks such as spooler,debugger etc., the number
    of system tasks should probably be increased.



    @148[ Module ]                          @052[ MM Object ]                     @001[ Overview ]
.151
    PG2000  MAIN MENU FUNCTIONS

    <OBJECT><Parameters><Configure><Module><B&R Module>:
    The maximum number of B&R modules (compiled tasks, exception handlers,
    runtime modules of function libraries etc.) which can be installed on the
    PCC is set in this entry field. The following formula applies for the
    minimum value:

    Cyclic Tasks + Idle Time Tasks + System Tasks + 10

    If you try to install more B&R modules than are defined in this entry field,
    the installation process is interrupted by an error message.









