    <OBJECT><Parameters><Configure><Timeouts><Allowed System Time Violation>:
    Analog to the TC cycle time, the system cycle time (10 msec operating system
    clock) is also monitored by the operating system. In order to prevent an
    immediate system cycle time violation during a short-term bottle neck 
    (e.g. if HS tasks and IRQ tasks use up the entire system time), you can 
    set an allowed system cycle time violation in 10 msec steps here. By doing
    this, a pre-defined system cycle time violation is allowed (simple
    system cycle time violation). However, if the allowed system cycle time
    violation is exceeded, the operating system triggers the exception "System
    Cycle Time Violation" (exception no. 162).









