    <OBJECT><Parameters><Configure><Timeouts><Wait>:
    After cold start: So that all modules of the controller can correctly finish
                      initialization after a cold start, the time defined
                      in this entry field must pass before the I/O and system 
                      modules of the PCC are first accessed.
    After warm start: So that all modules of the controller can correctly finish
                      initialization after a warm start, the time defined
                      in this entry field must pass before the I/O and system 
                      modules of the PCC are first accessed.
    At POWERFAIL:     A power failure is equated to a warm start. This means 
                      that the application is automatically started. For systems
                      with I/O bus expansion or remote I/O bus with different
                      power supply loads, it is possible that the current supply
                      for some components fails, whereas the main CPU still 
                      receives a supply.
                      If the main CPU recognizes the power failure of these
                      components before the local power supply also fails, a
                      fatal error is registered.

    @173[ Continue ]                        @052[ MM Object ]                     @001[ Overview ]
.173
    PG2000  MAIN MENU FUNCTIONS

                   In this case, the PCC re-boots in ERROR mode after the power
                   supply is returned, and then goes into SERVICE mode. This
                   means that the application is inactive and must be started
                   manually (by a warm start). To prevent the controller from
                   re-booting in SERVICE mode during a peripheral power failure,
                   you can set a delay parameter for the output of a fatal error
                   in this entry field. This means that if a fatal error occurs,
                   the time entered must pass to see if a power failure was the
                   cause of the error. If a power failure occurs during this
                   delay time, the fatal error is not reported and the 
                   controller re-boots with a warm start, once the power has 
                   returned, i.e. the application is automatically started.







