    <OBJECT><Compile>:              <F9>
    A compiler which compiles the application program (source, INIT SP) into
    the machine language of the processor (PCC) is called using this function.
    From this, an "EXECUTABLE MODULE" with the file name "*.BR" is produced,
    which can be downloaded to the PCC.
    The compilier process is influenced by the compiler options which have been
    set (see <Settings><Compiler>) function, and can be divided into individual
    sub-processes:
    - LINE PARSER:   Checks each SOURCE TEXT LINE for CORRECT syntax, and
                     enters unknown PVs in the databank.
    - BLOCK PARSER:  Checks a BLOCK (control structures, loops etc.) of the
                     source text for CORRECT syntax.
    - CODE GENERATOR:Creates an OBJECT FILE which contains the machine code and
                     the symbolic PV names. It also checks if all variables used
                     in the current databank have been declared.
    - TASK BUILDER:  Creates an EXECUTABLE MODULE (*.BR module) from the object
                     file and the information in the databank.


