    <OBJECT><Optimize>:
    All process variables (PVs) of the PCC or PROCESSOR OBJECT selected,which
    are no longer needed, are deleted from the databank (optimization of the
    DBK). A confirmation dialog box appears before deletion.

    This order is followed for databank optimization:
    - All PVs of the selected PCC or processor object available in the DBK
      are marked as "deletable".
    - Compilation of the individual tasks of the selected PCC or processor
      object. All needed PVs in the DBK are marked as "Reserved" during task
      compilation.
    - All PVs of the selected PCC or processor object which are marked as
      "deletable" are deleted. Therefore only the necessary PVs (marked as
      "Reserved") remain saved in the DBK.





