    <OBJECT><R U N>:                <F9>
    The application program (source, INIT SP) is compiled if necessary and is
    then downloaded to the PCC.

    - PREPARATION -> "VERSION" CHECK:
      If the task is unchanged, compilation is cancelled. If the executable
      modules (*.BR modules) are the same in PG and the PCC, downloading does
      not occur either.
    - PREPARATION -> COMPILING THE OBJECT:
      Ifthe source code or the task parameters were changed, the selected object
      is COMPILED in the PCC before downloading occurs.
    - DOWNLOADING THE EXECUTBLE MODULE:
      The executable *.BR module is TRANSFERRED to the PCC. The functions 
      "Download" and "Overload" are differentiated between when a task is 
      downloaded to application RAM. If an older version of the task already
      exists on the PCC, downloading occurs using the Overload function.
      However, if the task to be downloaded does not already exist on the PCC,
      The Download function is automatically used to download the task.

