    <PROJECT><Synchronize>:
    The following is valid for synchronization with a PCC 
    ("Synchronization with: PCC Online"):
    * All B&R modules (*.BR module = executable module) which are in the 
      application ROM, application RAM or FIX RAM of the PCC, but are not
      entered in the GDM, are uploaded from the PCC into the GDM and 
      displayed in the form of an object.
    * A dialog box for selecting the desired process appears for all modules
      with the same or different version numbers on the PCC and in the task
      layer (PG/PCC).
    * Objects (tasks) which were compiled with Rebuild Info (task parameters
      "Rebuild Info: On") are automatically decompiled with the setting
      "Reconstruct the Source: Yes", during Project Synchronization. This means
      that the source information about the B&R module (source, initialization
      sub-program, task parameters, variable declaration etc.) is restored.
      The task can then be changed.
    * Decompilation is not possible for objects without Rebuild Info (task
      parameters "Rebuild Info: Off"). In this case, a B&R object is entered 
      in the GDM for the respective module.
    @224[ Continue ]                       @053[ MM Project ]                     @001[ Overview ]
