.259
    PG2000  MAIN MENU FUNCTIONS

    <TARGET><Stop>:
    You can stop the PCC using this function (the term "Reset" was originally
    used for "Stop"). In the "Stop" mode, all battery-buffered RAM data
    (all tasks in application RAM, values of inputs, outputs and internals etc.)
    is kept (same as for "Warm Start" mode). After the "Stop" function has been
    called, the PCC goes intp Service mode, i.e. the application programs in
    application ROM, application RAM or FIX RAM are not started. Only the PCCSW
    runs in Service mode; all application programs are inactive.











                                      @054[ MM Target ]                     @001[ Overview ]
.260
    PG2000  MAIN MENU FUNCTIONS

    <TARGET><Warm start>:
    You can trigger a Warm Start on the PCC using this function.
    If a Warm Start occurs, all battery-buffered RAM data (all tasks in
    application RAM, values of inputs, outputs and internals etc.) is kept.
    Therefore, all tasks have the same state after a Warm Start (task active
    or task inactive) as they did before the Warm Start. Newly inserted system
    modules (remote master, network module etc.) are not recognized during a
    Warm Start. A Cold Start must be triggered for new system modules to be
    initialized.
    After a Warm Start, all tasks which were active before the Warm Start, are
    started. All available INIT SPs (also the INIT SPs in active tasks) are
    executed at the same time.







