    PG2000  MAIN MENU FUNCTIONS

    <TARGET><Service><Cold start>:
    The "Cold start" boot mode corresponds to a COMPLETE CPU initialization.
    The operating system is then started afresh, allocated memory is enabled
    and the system structures (all operating system information for orderly
    operation of the CPU) is recreated.
    In a cold start, all system modules (remote master, network module, etc.)
    are recognized and initialized. In addition, all modules stored in 
    application RAM are deleted (except for the modules in FIX RAM) and all
    process variables (inputs, outputs and internals) are initialized with zero.
    After a cold start, all tasks in application ROM or FIX RAM are started
    (requirement: task parameter <Installation> and <Start> set to "Default").
    All available initialization sub-programs (INIT SPs) are then executed.







