    <TARGET><Service><Diagnose>:
    The <System><Service><Diagnose> function is also used if a defective
    B&R module (stored in application ROM or FIX RAM) prevents correct boot-up.
    To avoid erasing the entire application ROM or FIX ROM in this case, you
    must re-boot the PCC in Diagnose mode. The PCC only boots with the operating
    software in Diagnose mode, i.e. all B&R modules in application RAM and
    ROM are ignored and are therefore rendered inactive. This also guarantees
    that the defect B&R module is not referenced.











