    <TARGET><Service><Erase FIXRAM>:
    You can erase the entire contents of FIX RAM using this function.
    After FIX RAM has been erased, a Cold Start is automatically executed.
    For this reason, you are advised that all data in application RAM
    will be lost if this function is used, when the <System><Service>
    <Erase FIXRAM> function is called!

    FIX RAM is that part of application RAM which behaves like application ROM
    during a Cold Start. This means that B&R modules which are stored in
    FIX RAM are not erased during a Cold Start.









