    <TARGET><Service><Erase perm. memory>:
    From version 1.91 of the PCCSW onwards, a memory block which is not erased
    during a Cold Start either (permanent memory), can be defined on the PCC.
    This permanent memory can be deleted using the <System><Service>
    <Erase perm. memory> function. 
    After the permanent memory has been erased, a Cold Start is automatically
    executed. For this reason, you are advised that all data in
    application RAM will be lost if the <System><Service><Erase perm. memory>
    function is called!

    The size of the permanent memory can be set in the system configuration.
    To do this, call the <Object><Parameters> function from the task layer
    of the GDM. The cursor must be on the "sysconf" object. Then the size of
    the permanent memory can be set by selecting the <Memory> function from
    the pop-up menu of the <Configuration> box. 
    The respective input fields are only enabled from version 1.91 of the
    PCCSW onwards!


