.270
    PG2000  MAIN MENU FUNCTIONS

    <TARGET><Service><Update PCCSW>:
    The operating system PCCSW can be transferred to the APM, or an operating
    system update can be carried out using this function. 

    PREPARATORY STEPS by the user:
    1. The PROGRAMMING PROTECTION SWITCH on the APM front must be in write
       position.
    2. Control of the BOOTMAN SWITCH POSITION behind the APM side window:
       - for FLASH APM, which is already programmed (operating system update),
         the Bootman switch must be in the "ERASE" position!
       - for empty FLASH APM (operating system download), the Bootman switch
         position can also be in switch position "OK"!
    3. Call the <Target><Service><Update PCCSW> function.

    If these steps are not carried out, no PG/Bootman connection is made.
    In this case, no operating system update or operating system download
    is possible!


