    <Spooling>:    
    * After download:   The compiled object is spooled IMMEDIATELY after
                        download to the specified I/O processor (slot known).
    - After warm start: The compiled object is first downloaded to the CPU.
                        The spooling process from the CPU to the IO processor
                        only takes place after a warm start (see function
                        <Target><Warm start>).
    - Never:            With this setting, the object is neither spooled to the
                        IO processor after download, or during a warm start.
                        Therefore, it is possible to work exculsively with the
                        I/O processor library (spool library).

   




