.371
    G D M - BASICS

    <Layers>       :   The GDM is divided into THREE types of LAYERS: a
                       PCC layer, Processor layer and a Task layer.
                       The GDM can have more than one processor layer and task
                       layer, depending on the number of PCCs and processors
                       You can move between the layers with:
                       Layer : PCC LAYER -> (PROCESSOR) -> TASK LAYER -> TASK
                       Layer : TASK LAYER -> (PROCESSOR) -> PCC LAYER
                     
    <OBJECTS>:         Objects are SYMBOLICALLY represented in the GDM. 
                       (e.g.: PCCs, processors, tasks, BR modules etc.)

                       The term "Object" has a different meaning in each layer.
