.491
    PL2000 Syntax:  CALLING FUNCTION BLOCKS

    All input and output parameters for a FBK call must be put inside
    brackets () or as parameters of an ALIAS structure. 
    FUNCTION BLOCKS have NO RETURN VALUE.
    Only function blocks can be presently created by the user.

    - <FBK CALL> with complete IN/OUT parameter list:
      fbkx(in1, in2,..., out_1, out_2)  ; 'fbkx' is the FBK name
                                        ; in1,in2, ... input parameter
                                        ; out_1, ..... output parameter

    - <FBK ALIAS Call>:
      The FBK parameters can be addressed as structure components of
      the alias structure with "aliasname.paramname":
      alias_n.in1 = 1                   ; in1 is input parameter of fbkx
      alias_n.in2 = 0                   ; in2 is input parameter of fbkx
      :                                 ; 'alias_n': name of the FBK structure
      alias_n  FBK fbkx()               ; 'fbkx' is the name of the FBK
      result = alias_n.out1             ; out1 is output parameter of fbkx

    @490[ Calling FBKs ]                  @420[ PL2000 Syntax ]                   @001[ Overview ]
.492
    PL2000 Syntax:  EINBINDEN VON FUNCTIONS

    All standard library FUNCTIONS can be used via the following function
    call in the application program.
    FUNCTIONS ONLY have ONE RETURN parameter. This is returned by the function.

    - <FUNCTION Call> with complete IN parameter list:

      Result = funct(in1, in2,...)   ; 'fbkx' is the name of the FBK
                                     ; in1, in2, ... input parameter
                                     ; Result    ... contains output parameters
                                                     after the function has been
                                                     called








    @490[ Calling FBKs ]                  @420[ PL2000 Syntax ]                   @001[ Overview ]
