.528
    AWL - BEFEHLE

    STL commands are KEY WORDS of STATEMENT LIST programming and are entered
    in the OPERATOR FIELD.

    Syntax checking and compilation:
    - The STL SYNTAX is only CHECKED by the STL parser when the file is SAVED.
      Any errors and warnings are shown in the message window.
    - A COMPILER run for STL consists of the parser, code generator and task
      builder. The variables are known after the parser run and can then be
      declared.

    The following POINTS are to be NOTED for STL programming:
    - There is only ONE REGISTER => the ACCUMULATOR available in STL.
      (no address register or extended address types)
    - ADDRESSING in the STL occurs via VARIABLES and CONSTANTS.
    - The current RESULT of a statement line is stored in the ACCUMULATOR.
    - The KEY WORDS are NOT case sensitive.
    - FUNCTION BLOCKS can be called in different ways.


