.541
    STL - SYNTAX:  CALLING FUNCTION BLOCKS

    All FBK input and output parameters must be either transferred when the FBK
    is called or as a parameter of an ALIAS structure.
    A FUNCTION BLOCK CALL does not change the Accumulator (no RETURN VALUE) !

    - <FBK CALL> with complete IN/OUT parameter list:
       CAL  fbkx(in1, in2,..., out_1)(* 'fbkx' is the name of the FBK;    *)
                                     (* in1,in2,.. In parameter of fbkx   *)
                                     (* out_1,.... Out parameter of fbkx  *)
    - <FBK ALIAS CALL>:
       The FBK parameters can be addressed as structure components
       of the alias structure with "aliasname.paramname"
       LD       1
       ST       alias_n.in1          (* in1 ist In parameter of fbkx      *)
       LD       0
       ST       alias_n.in2          (* in2 is in parameter of fbkx      *)
       :                             (* 'alias_n': name of the FBK structure  *)
       alias_n  FBK fbkx()           (* 'fbkx' is the name of the FBK;      *)
       LD       alias_n.out1         (* out1 is out parameter of fbkx    *)

