.542
    STL - SYNTAX:  CALLING FUNCTIONS

    All standard library FUNCTIONS can be used via the following function
    call in an application program.
    FUNCTIONS ONLY have ONE RETURN parameter that is sent back to the
    ACCUMULATOR as the RETURN VALUE.

    <FUNCTIONS / Inline FBKs>:
     - When calling FUNCTIONS the ACCUMULATOR is transferred as the FIRST
       PARAMETER. If more parameters are required, they are entered WITHOUT 
       BRACKETS but separated with COMMAS. After the call the RESULT is 
       located in the ACCUMULATOR.

       LD       pv1               (* 1. INPUT parameter in the Accumulator    *)
       funct_x  pv2, pv3, pv4
       ST       ergebnis          (* Save the ACCUMULATOR as result           *)


       These three lines would be written in PL2000 syntax as follows:
       Result = funct_x(pv1, pv2, pv3, pv4)

