    STL - SYNTAX:  COMPLEX DATA TYPES

    <ARRAY>     :        Array Name[Element Index]

      An array consists of defined number of elements of the SAME DATA TYPE.
      The elements of an array can have any data type, including a structure.
      Individual elements of an array are addressed and accessed using the
      ARRAY NAME and the ELEMENT INDEX [in square brackets]:


    <STRUCTURE> :        Structure Name.Component Name

      A structure is a collection of elements. The elements can be ANY ANALOG
      DATA TYPE, ARRAY or other STRUCTURE. An individual element of a structure
      is referenced by the STRUCTURE NAME (variable name) and the COMPONENT
      NAME. To address an individual element, enter the structure name and the
      component name separated by a FULL STOP ".":
      (e.g. also: structure name.array name[element index])



