    L A D  -  FOOT LINE MENU FUNCTIONS

    <Contact>:     PLACE A LAD CONTACT

       A selection window appears showing all available contacts. The desired
       object can be selected with the cursor keys or the mouse. You can also
       insert contacts via hotkeys, without the selection window
       (see @640[LAD Objects]). When a contact has been inserted, a window appears.
       Here, you either enter a constant value or a variable name (max. 10
       characters) for the contact. You confirm the entry with <Enter>. The
       contact is placed at the current cursor position (also in fields which
       contain lines). The cursor is then moved right.


    <FBK>:  PLACE A FUNCTION BLOCK

       A selection window containing all available function blocks appears.
       The desired function block can be selected from the list. If possible,
       the FBK is inserted in the LAD, so that the top left corner is at the
       cursor position.

