.632
    L A D  -  CONVENTIONS

    The following conventions are checked and reported when a LADDER DIAGRAM
    is created:

    Restrictions on placing the contact at the cursor position:
      - Outputs are not allowed in column 1
      - Analog inputs are only allowed in column 1.

    - Restrictions on placing a FBK (cursor position = top left corner):
      - FBK does not have enough room (e.g. was covered by another LAD symbol).
      - FBKs not in column 1 (no inputs can be connected).
      - FBKs not in the second to last column (no outputs can be connected).

    Error checking before the LAD is SAVED:

    - Missing outputs
    - Open lines (output missing)
    - Nameless contacts
    - Function blocks without inputs or outputs

