.731
    FBK - CREATION

    There is a CERTAIN PROCEDURE to be followed when CREATING NEW FBKs:

    1.) CREATE FBK SOURCE:    Syntax: PL2000, STL or LAD

        After loading or creating a new FBK, the appropriate source code
        editor is called.
        The FBK source is created with the respective syntax of the selected
        programming language.


    2.) VARIABLE DECLARATION:   Scope: LOCAL or DYNAMIC

        Only PVs defined in the variable declaration can be connected as
        inputs or outputs in the FBK mask.
        The PVs defined for the FBKs are always COMPLETELY SEPARATE from all
        other project variables.
        


