    FBK   - MASKS

    - Using the FBK MASK, the INPUT/OUTPUT ASSIGNMENT of the INTERNAL FBK
      VARIABLES is carried out.

    - ONLY PVs declared in the VD can be used as inputs/outputs. These PVs are
      displayed in a selection list when a FBK connection is inserted.
      (PVs which are already connected are no longer displayed in the list).

    - INTERNAL FBK VARIABLES are COMPLETELY SEPARATE from the variables
      which are connected to the FBK connections later.

    - The ORDER of the PVs later connected to the FBK depends on the 
      connection order (from TOP to BOTTOM) of the FBK parameters.

    - The FBK mask is defined in the FBK editor.

    - The SYNTAX is automatically retained by the FBK editor.  The FBK borders
      and the connection area are automatically extended/reduced when
      inserting/deleting occurs.

