      ' ' ... indicates a STRING ENTRY WITHOUT NULL-TERMINATION 'string'


    @781[< Syntax for NUMERICAL ENTRIES >:]
    - There are 4 INPUT FORMATS to choose from - decimal/hex/binary/float
    - The DATA TYPE of the entries comes from the LENGTH and VALUE of the ENTRY


    @782[< Syntax for SPECIAL CHARACTERS >:]
    - Special characters in strings can be entered in "C Format".


    Example:    ; Data Module - Example (comment line)
                2,15,"This is a string",$1234, %%10011010

