.781
    DATA MODULE - SYNTAX

     Syntax of the numerical entries in the data module
     * DECIMAL : (-)dddd       d ... 0 - 9
          BYTE : Number of digits <= 3, value < 256   or > -128
          WORD : Number of digits <= 5, value < 65536 or > -32268
          LONG : when the WORD limit is exceeded

     * HEX     : $xxxx         x ... 0 - 9, A - F (2,4 or 8 digits)
          BYTE : Number of digits 2
          WORD : Number of digits 4
          LONG : Number of digits 8

     * BINARY  : %%bbbbbbbb      b ... 0,1  (8, 16 or 32 digits !!)
          BYTE : Number of digits 8
          WORD : Number of digits 16
          LONG : Number of digits 32

     * FLOAT   :   ff.ff          f ... 0 - 9
            Float values are characterized by a decimal point.

