.785
    DATA MODULE - USE

    Data modules can be created both for the PCC CPU (spool adr. = 0) and for
    intelligent controllers (spool adr. = position of the controller).
    (Use: DA_info()..assign a dynamic variable to the data module,...)

    FUNCTION OVERVIEW:
    status = DA_create(adr(name),grp,spadr,dlng,adr(data),adr(modat),adr(ident))
    status = DA_write(ident,adr(data),dlng,mo_offs)
    status = DA_ident(adr(name),grp,adr(ident))
    status = DA_delete(ident)
    status = DA_burn(ident)
    status = DA_info(ident,adr(dadr),adr(dlen),adr(mem_typ))

    PARAMETERS
      name...BYTE field / "module name" data.....BYTE stream  data area
      grp....BYTE  group number         modat....LONG  module data address
      spadr..WORD  spool address        ident....LONG  Identifier
      dlng...LONG  data length          mo_offs..LONG  Offset in data area
      dadr...LONG  data area address    mem_typ..BYTE  (1=RAM,2=EPROM)

    @786[ Example ]                    @770[ DATA MODULE Editor ]                 @001[ Overview ]
.786
    DATA MODULE - USE
    VD:     NAME       Scope       Data Type  Length    I/O Type
            da_ptr     Dynamic     da_struct    10      Reference
            da_adr     Local       LONG         1       INTERNAL
            :          :           :            :       :
    TASK:   ;---------------------- INIT SECTION: ------------------------
            status = DA_ident("module name",0,adr(ident))
            if status = 0 then                 ; data module found ?
                status = DA_info(ident,adr(da_adr),adr(lng),adr(memtyp))
                if status <> 0 then
                    da_adr = 0                 ; ==> NO data module access
                else
                    da_ptr access da_adr       ; ==> Assign CORRECT ADRESS
            else
                da_adr = 0                     ; ==> NO data module access
            endif
            ;-------------------- CYCLIC SECTION: --------------------
            if da_adr <> 0 then                ; data module access allowed ?
                ; READ from the data module with da_ptr[index].element
                ; WRITE to the data module using the DA_write() function
            endif
