.932
    PG2000 - DIALOG BOX

    Using the KEYBOARD:

    - Using the selection help: highlight the desired list entry using
      the starting letter.
    - Suggested correct entries do not have to be defined.
    - You can confirm the dialog box entries with ^<ENTER>, without moving
      the cursor to the OK filed. The OK field must be highlighted (can be
      changed with <TAB>).


    Using the MOUSE:

    - A mouse click causes:
      - The selection of a FIELD to make an entry
      - A direct confirmation of a POP-UP WINDOW function, and its display in
        the dialog box.
      - The execution of the CONFIRMATION which was clicked (OK, Cancel)
      - Suggested correct entries do not have to be defined.

